    • Constructor Detail

      • Formula2SQL

        public Formula2SQL(Set<Variable> projection,
                   RDBMSDatabase database)
        Convert a formula to a query that will fetch all possible combinations of constants used in that formual (aka grounding). This variant will enforce unqiue results (DISTINCT).
        Parameters:
        projection - the collection of variables (columns) to return (the variable's name will be used as the column alias). If not set, all columns (*) will be retutned.
        database - the database to query over. The read and write partitions will be picked up from here.

      • Formula2SQL

        public Formula2SQL(Set<Variable> projection,
                   RDBMSDatabase database,
                   boolean isDistinct)
        See above description.
        Parameters:
        isDistinct - true if you want to enforce unique results (DISTINCT), false otherwise. Warning: this can be a costly operation.

      • Formula2SQL

        public Formula2SQL(Set<Variable> projection,
                   RDBMSDatabase database,
                   boolean isDistinct,
                   Atom lazyTarget)
        See above description.
        Parameters:
        lazyTarget - if this is non-null, then this formula will be treated as a partial grounding query. This means that we will treat Partition.LAZY_PARTITION_ID as a valid partition, and this atom will be exclusivley drawn from Partition.LAZY_PARTITION_ID. We will do a DIRECT REFERENCE comparison against atoms in the formual to check for this specific one.
